:"A common transition is one which is accessible from all or selected statuses in the workflow.","zp.blueprint.transhelpcommontransdef2":"For example, consider the workflow of a document review process. The review can be put on hold any time in the process. In this case, Suspend is set as a common transition from all statuses to the On hold status.","zp.blueprint.transhelpdef":"A transition is the connecting link between two statuses. A {0} advances to the next status when you perform a transition.","zp.blueprint.transhelpduringdef1":"Fields and messages are displayed when a transition is being performed in the {0} details page.","zp.blueprint.transhelpduringdef2":"For example, <b>Attachment</b> can be added as a mandatory field for the users to attach their documents for review.","zp.blueprint.transhelpduringdef3":"The user who performs the transition from the {0} details page will have to provide the necessary inputs to the field. The message that is configured will be displayed while performing the transition.","zp.blueprint.transhelppts1":"There are Before, During, and After transition phases that you can configure for a transition.","zp.blueprint.transhelppts2":"Transitions are displayed as buttons in the {0} details page. Click on the transition button to perform the transition and the status will be updated.","zp.blueprint.transhelpstatusdef":"A status represents the current position of a {0} in the workflow. To create a blueprint, drag and drop statuses from the <em>Available Status</em> section and connect the nodes between the statuses.","zp.blueprint.transhelpstatusdefeg":"To add new status, you can simply drag a node from a status or click <b>Add</b> in the <em>Available Status</em> section.","zp.blueprint.transition":"Transition","zp.blueprint.transitionactivity":"transition","zp.blueprint.transitiondelete":"Are you sure you want to delete this transition?","zp.blueprint.transitionnamelabel":"Transition Name","zp.blueprint.transitionorder":"Transitions 